<% details = legal_details(region) %>
<% config = RegionHelper.region_config(region) %>

<div class="legal-document">
  <div class="legal-header">
    <h1>Lender Agreement</h1>
    <p class="legal-subtitle">Equity Preservation Mortgage Platform &mdash; Lender Participation Agreement</p>
    <p class="legal-jurisdiction"><%= config["name"] %> &mdash; <%= config["code"] %></p>
    <p class="legal-version">Version <%= legal_version %> | Effective: <%= legal_date %></p>
    <p class="legal-regulated">Regulated by: <%= details[:regulator] %></p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-body">

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 1. PARTIES                                                          -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>1. PARTIES</h2>
    <p><strong>1.1</strong> <strong>The Lender:</strong> [Lender Name], (<%= details[:company_registration] %>: [Number]), licensed under <%= details[:licensing_act] %>, of [Registered Address] (the &ldquo;<strong>Lender</strong>&rdquo;).</p>
    <p><strong>1.2</strong> <strong>The Platform Operator:</strong> FutureProof Financial Ltd, (<%= details[:company_registration] %>: [Number]), operating the FutureProof Equity Preservation Mortgage Platform at www.futureprooffinancial.co (the &ldquo;<strong>Platform</strong>&rdquo; or &ldquo;<strong>FutureProof</strong>&rdquo;).</p>
    <p><strong>1.3</strong> The Lender and FutureProof are collectively referred to as the &ldquo;<strong>Parties</strong>&rdquo; and individually as a &ldquo;<strong>Party</strong>&rdquo;.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 2. PURPOSE & SCOPE                                                  -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>2. PURPOSE &amp; SCOPE</h2>
    <p><strong>2.1</strong> This Agreement establishes the terms under which the Lender shall originate, administer, and service Equity Preservation Mortgages (&ldquo;<strong>EPMs</strong>&rdquo;) through the Platform in the jurisdiction of <%= config["name"] %>.</p>
    <p><strong>2.2</strong> The Platform provides the technology infrastructure, borrower acquisition, EPM calculation engine, investment management, and regulatory compliance framework within which the Lender operates.</p>
    <p><strong>2.3</strong> The Lender shall originate EPM loans exclusively through the Platform and in accordance with the Platform&rsquo;s approved lending standards, product specifications, and the requirements of <%= details[:consumer_credit_act] %>.</p>
    <p><strong>2.4</strong> This Agreement does not create a partnership, joint venture, or agency relationship between the Parties except as expressly set out herein.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 3. DEFINITIONS                                                      -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>3. DEFINITIONS</h2>
    <p><strong>3.1</strong> In this Agreement, unless the context otherwise requires:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Approved Valuer&rdquo;</strong> means a property valuer meeting the qualifications and panel requirements set out in Schedule 2;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Borrower&rdquo;</strong> means a natural person who enters into an EPM loan agreement with the Lender through the Platform;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Business Day&rdquo;</strong> means a day (other than a Saturday, Sunday, or public holiday) on which banks are open for general business in <%= config["name"] %>;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Commencement Date&rdquo;</strong> means the date specified in Schedule 1 or, if not specified, the date of execution of this Agreement;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Credit Assessment&rdquo;</strong> means the assessment of a Borrower&rsquo;s creditworthiness conducted in accordance with Clause 8;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;EPM&rdquo;</strong> or <strong>&ldquo;Equity Preservation Mortgage&rdquo;</strong> means a mortgage product under which a portion of the loan amount is invested in a diversified portfolio to preserve or grow the Borrower&rsquo;s equity over the loan term;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;EPM Income&rdquo;</strong> means income generated by the invested portion of the EPM, distributed in accordance with the Payments Waterfall;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Facility Limit&rdquo;</strong> means the maximum aggregate principal amount of EPM loans the Lender is authorised to originate under this Agreement, as specified in Schedule 1;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Investment Portfolio&rdquo;</strong> means the portfolio of investments managed by the Platform on behalf of EPM Borrowers, comprising approximately 70% equity index funds (S&amp;P 500 ETFs or equivalent) and 30% fixed income instruments;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;LMI&rdquo;</strong> means Lenders Mortgage Insurance;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Loan-to-Value Ratio&rdquo;</strong> or <strong>&ldquo;LTV&rdquo;</strong> means the ratio of the loan principal to the value of the secured property, not to exceed <%= (config["max_ltv"].to_f * 100).to_i %>%;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Origination Fee&rdquo;</strong> means the fee payable by the Borrower to the Lender upon settlement of an EPM loan, as specified in the Fee Schedule;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Payments Waterfall&rdquo;</strong> means the order of priority for distribution of EPM Income, being: (i) mortgage repayment obligations, (ii) platform fees, (iii) investment management fees, (iv) surplus to Borrower;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Platform Standards&rdquo;</strong> means the lending criteria, operational procedures, and compliance requirements published by FutureProof from time to time;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Pool Coverage&rdquo;</strong> means the mechanism maintained by the Platform to manage investment shortfall risk across the EPM portfolio;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Responsible Lending Obligations&rdquo;</strong> means the obligations imposed on the Lender under <%= details[:consumer_credit_act] %>;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Run-off&rdquo;</strong> means the period following termination during which existing EPM loans continue to be serviced to maturity;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Secured Property&rdquo;</strong> means the residential <%= config["property_term"] %> over which a mortgage is granted to secure an EPM loan;</li>
      <li><strong>&ldquo;Settlement&rdquo;</strong> means the completion and funding of an EPM loan.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 4. LENDER OBLIGATIONS                                               -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>4. LENDER OBLIGATIONS</h2>
    <p><strong>4.1</strong> The Lender shall at all times:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) maintain all licences, registrations, and authorisations required under <%= details[:licensing_act] %> to originate and administer mortgage loans in <%= config["name"] %>;</li>
      <li>(b) comply with all applicable requirements of <%= details[:consumer_credit_act] %>;</li>
      <li>(c) originate EPM loans in strict accordance with the Platform Standards and underwriting criteria set out in this Agreement;</li>
      <li>(d) employ suitably qualified and trained staff to assess, originate, and administer EPM loans;</li>
      <li>(e) maintain adequate professional indemnity insurance with a minimum cover of <%= config["currency_symbol"] %>[Amount];</li>
      <li>(f) provide FutureProof with prompt written notice of any material change to its licensing status, financial condition, or regulatory standing;</li>
      <li>(g) not assign, delegate, or sub-contract any of its obligations under this Agreement without the prior written consent of FutureProof;</li>
      <li>(h) maintain adequate capital reserves as required by applicable prudential regulations;</li>
      <li>(i) implement and maintain systems and controls commensurate with the nature and scale of its EPM lending operations.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>4.2</strong> The Lender shall notify FutureProof immediately upon becoming aware of any regulatory investigation, enforcement action, or material complaint relating to its EPM lending activities.</p>
    <p><strong>4.3</strong> The Lender shall participate in Platform training and accreditation programmes as reasonably required by FutureProof.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 5. PLATFORM OBLIGATIONS                                             -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>5. PLATFORM OBLIGATIONS</h2>
    <p><strong>5.1</strong> FutureProof shall:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) provide and maintain the technology platform through which EPM loans are originated, managed, and serviced;</li>
      <li>(b) manage the Investment Portfolio in accordance with the EPM product specification and applicable regulations;</li>
      <li>(c) calculate and distribute EPM Income in accordance with the Payments Waterfall;</li>
      <li>(d) maintain the Pool Coverage mechanism to manage investment shortfall risk;</li>
      <li>(e) provide the Lender with access to real-time portfolio dashboards, reporting tools, and borrower management interfaces;</li>
      <li>(f) manage all borrower-facing communications relating to the investment component of EPMs;</li>
      <li>(g) maintain all necessary licences and registrations to operate the Platform in <%= config["name"] %>;</li>
      <li>(h) provide regulatory compliance support, including template documentation, disclosure frameworks, and compliance monitoring;</li>
      <li>(i) procure Lenders Mortgage Insurance on all EPM loans at a rate of 2% of the loan amount.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>5.2</strong> FutureProof shall use commercially reasonable efforts to maintain Platform availability of 99.5% uptime, measured on a monthly basis, excluding scheduled maintenance windows.</p>
    <p><strong>5.3</strong> FutureProof shall notify the Lender of any material changes to Platform Standards not less than [30] days prior to implementation.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 6. LOAN ORIGINATION STANDARDS                                       -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>6. LOAN ORIGINATION STANDARDS</h2>
    <p><strong>6.1</strong> The Lender shall originate EPM loans only to Borrowers who:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) are natural persons aged 18 years or over;</li>
      <li>(b) are residents of or hold valid visa/immigration status in <%= config["name"] %>;</li>
      <li>(c) own or are purchasing a residential <%= config["property_term"] %> with a minimum value of <%= config["currency_symbol"] %><%= number_with_delimiter(config["min_home_value"]) %>;</li>
      <li>(d) satisfy the Credit Assessment requirements set out in Clause 8;</li>
      <li>(e) have received and acknowledged all required product disclosures.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>6.2</strong> The maximum loan amount for any single EPM shall not exceed the lesser of:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) <%= (config["max_ltv"].to_f * 100).to_i %>% of the Approved Valuation of the Secured Property; or</li>
      <li>(b) the maximum amount specified in the Fee Schedule.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>6.3</strong> Available EPM loan terms are 10, 15, 20, 25, or 30 years.</p>
    <p><strong>6.4</strong> The Lender shall process all EPM applications through the Platform&rsquo;s origination workflow and shall not circumvent or bypass any Platform controls or checks.</p>
    <p><strong>6.5</strong> The Lender shall maintain complete and accurate records of each EPM application, including all supporting documentation, for a minimum period of [7] years from the date of settlement or rejection.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 7. UNDERWRITING REQUIREMENTS                                        -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>7. UNDERWRITING REQUIREMENTS</h2>
    <p><strong>7.1</strong> The Lender shall apply the following underwriting criteria to all EPM applications:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) verification of identity in accordance with <%= details[:aml_act] %> requirements;</li>
      <li>(b) assessment of income, employment, and financial position;</li>
      <li>(c) review of existing liabilities and debt service commitments;</li>
      <li>(d) credit bureau inquiry and assessment of credit history;</li>
      <li>(e) independent property valuation by an Approved Valuer;</li>
      <li>(f) assessment of the Borrower&rsquo;s understanding of the EPM product, including the investment component and associated risks.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>7.2</strong> The Lender shall not approve an EPM application where:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) the Borrower does not meet the minimum credit score threshold specified in the Platform Standards;</li>
      <li>(b) the Borrower&rsquo;s debt-to-income ratio exceeds the maximum permitted by the Platform Standards;</li>
      <li>(c) the Secured Property does not meet the Platform&rsquo;s property eligibility criteria;</li>
      <li>(d) the Lender has reason to believe the application is fraudulent or the Borrower has provided materially false information.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>7.3</strong> All underwriting decisions shall be documented and retained on the Platform in accordance with regulatory record-keeping requirements.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 8. CREDIT ASSESSMENT                                                -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>8. CREDIT ASSESSMENT</h2>
    <p><strong>8.1</strong> The Lender shall conduct a comprehensive Credit Assessment for each EPM application in compliance with its Responsible Lending Obligations under <%= details[:consumer_credit_act] %>.</p>
    <p><strong>8.2</strong> The Credit Assessment shall include, at minimum:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) verification that the EPM loan is not unsuitable for the Borrower, having regard to the Borrower&rsquo;s requirements, objectives, and financial situation;</li>
      <li>(b) an assessment of the Borrower&rsquo;s capacity to meet repayment obligations over the full loan term without substantial hardship;</li>
      <li>(c) consideration of the Borrower&rsquo;s likely future financial circumstances, including foreseeable changes in income or expenses;</li>
      <li>(d) where the Borrower is nearing retirement age, assessment of income adequacy post-retirement.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>8.3</strong> The Lender shall make reasonable inquiries about, and take reasonable steps to verify, the Borrower&rsquo;s financial situation before entering into an EPM loan.</p>
    <p><strong>8.4</strong> The Lender shall document and retain evidence of each Credit Assessment, including the basis for the lending decision, for the period required by applicable law.</p>

    <% if region.to_s == 'us' %>
    <p><strong>8.5</strong> The Lender shall comply with the Ability-to-Repay/Qualified Mortgage standards established under Section 1411 of the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act and Regulation Z (12 CFR 1026.43).</p>
    <p><strong>8.6</strong> The Lender shall provide Borrowers with a Loan Estimate within three (3) business days of receiving a completed application, and a Closing Disclosure at least three (3) business days before settlement, in accordance with the TILA-RESPA Integrated Disclosure (TRID) rules.</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'au' %>
    <p><strong>8.5</strong> The Lender shall comply with the responsible lending conduct obligations in Part 3-1 of the National Consumer Credit Protection Act 2009 (Cth), including the requirement to make a preliminary assessment that the credit contract is &ldquo;not unsuitable&rdquo; for the consumer.</p>
    <p><strong>8.6</strong> The Lender shall have regard to ASIC Regulatory Guide 209 (Credit licensing: Responsible lending conduct) in discharging its responsible lending obligations.</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'nz' %>
    <p><strong>8.5</strong> The Lender shall comply with the lender responsibility principles set out in Part 1A of the Credit Contracts and Consumer Finance Act 2003 (CCCFA), including the duty to exercise the care, diligence, and skill of a responsible lender.</p>
    <p><strong>8.6</strong> The Lender shall comply with the Responsible Lending Code issued under section 9F of the CCCFA as applicable to EPM products.</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'uk' %>
    <p><strong>8.5</strong> The Lender shall conduct an affordability assessment in accordance with MCOB 11 (Responsible lending and financing) and ensure that the EPM loan is affordable for the Borrower over the full term.</p>
    <p><strong>8.6</strong> The Lender shall comply with the FCA Consumer Duty (PS22/9) including the obligation to act to deliver good outcomes for retail customers, ensure products provide fair value, and support customer understanding.</p>
    <p><strong>8.7</strong> The Lender shall comply with the Mortgage Market Review (MMR) requirements, including full income verification and interest rate stress testing.</p>
    <% end %>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 9. PROPERTY VALUATION                                               -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>9. PROPERTY VALUATION</h2>
    <p><strong>9.1</strong> Each Secured Property shall be valued by an Approved Valuer prior to settlement of the EPM loan.</p>
    <p><strong>9.2</strong> The valuation must be:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) conducted no more than [90] days prior to the date of settlement;</li>
      <li>(b) performed on a market value basis, reflecting the price the property would achieve if sold on the open market;</li>
      <li>(c) compliant with applicable valuation standards in <%= config["name"] %>;</li>
      <li>(d) independent of the Lender, the Borrower, and any party with a financial interest in the transaction.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>9.3</strong> The Lender shall not accept a valuation where the Approved Valuer has disclosed a conflict of interest or where there are material concerns regarding the valuation methodology.</p>
    <p><strong>9.4</strong> The Lender may, at its discretion or at FutureProof&rsquo;s request, commission a second valuation where:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) the initial valuation differs materially from the Borrower&rsquo;s estimated property value;</li>
      <li>(b) market conditions have changed significantly since the valuation date;</li>
      <li>(c) the Secured Property has unusual characteristics that may affect its market value.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>9.5</strong> The property must be a residential <%= config["property_term"] %> in <%= config["name"] %> with a minimum value of <%= config["currency_symbol"] %><%= number_with_delimiter(config["min_home_value"]) %> and a maximum value of <%= config["currency_symbol"] %><%= number_with_delimiter(config["max_home_value"]) %>.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 10. LOAN DOCUMENTATION                                              -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>10. LOAN DOCUMENTATION</h2>
    <p><strong>10.1</strong> The Lender shall use the Platform&rsquo;s approved EPM loan documentation, which includes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) EPM Loan Agreement;</li>
      <li>(b) Mortgage or Deed of Trust (as applicable);</li>
      <li>(c) EPM Product Disclosure Statement;</li>
      <li>(d) Investment Component Disclosure;</li>
      <li>(e) Borrower Acknowledgement of Risks;</li>
      <li>(f) Direct Debit / Payment Authority;</li>
      <li>(g) Privacy Consent and Disclosure;</li>
      <li>(h) Beneficiary Nomination Form.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>10.2</strong> The Lender shall ensure that all loan documentation is:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) completed accurately and in full;</li>
      <li>(b) executed by all required parties;</li>
      <li>(c) provided to the Borrower within the timeframes required by applicable law;</li>
      <li>(d) retained in accordance with regulatory record-keeping obligations.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>10.3</strong> The Lender shall provide the Borrower with a copy of all executed loan documentation within [5] Business Days of settlement.</p>
    <p><strong>10.4</strong> The Lender shall not modify the approved loan documentation without the prior written consent of FutureProof.</p>

    <% if region.to_s == 'us' %>
    <p><strong>10.5</strong> The Lender shall provide all disclosures required under the Truth in Lending Act (TILA), the Real Estate Settlement Procedures Act (RESPA), and applicable state lending laws, including the Loan Estimate, Closing Disclosure, and any required state-specific disclosures.</p>
    <p><strong>10.6</strong> The Lender shall comply with the Equal Credit Opportunity Act (ECOA) and the Home Mortgage Disclosure Act (HMDA) in all EPM origination activities.</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'au' %>
    <p><strong>10.5</strong> The Lender shall provide a Credit Guide in accordance with section 126 of the National Consumer Credit Protection Act 2009 (Cth) before providing credit assistance to the Borrower.</p>
    <p><strong>10.6</strong> The Lender shall ensure that Key Facts Sheets are provided in accordance with Division 2A of Part 3-2 of the National Credit Code.</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'nz' %>
    <p><strong>10.5</strong> The Lender shall provide the Borrower with initial disclosure and continuing disclosure as required under Parts 2 and 3 of the Credit Contracts and Consumer Finance Act 2003 (CCCFA).</p>
    <p><strong>10.6</strong> Disclosure shall include the <%= details[:interest_disclosure] %> as required by the CCCFA and shall be in a format that is clear, concise, and effective.</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'uk' %>
    <p><strong>10.5</strong> The Lender shall provide the Borrower with a Key Facts Illustration (KFI) in accordance with MCOB 5 and a binding mortgage offer in accordance with MCOB 6.</p>
    <p><strong>10.6</strong> The Lender shall comply with the European Standardised Information Sheet (ESIS) requirements as applicable under retained EU law and MCOB 5A.</p>
    <% end %>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 11. FUNDING & SETTLEMENT                                            -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>11. FUNDING &amp; SETTLEMENT</h2>
    <p><strong>11.1</strong> Upon approval of an EPM application, the Lender shall fund the loan in accordance with the settlement process set out in Schedule 3.</p>
    <p><strong>11.2</strong> At settlement, the loan proceeds shall be allocated as follows:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) the portion required to acquire or refinance the Secured Property shall be disbursed to the vendor or existing mortgagee;</li>
      <li>(b) the investment component shall be transferred to the Platform&rsquo;s Investment Portfolio for management in accordance with the EPM product specification;</li>
      <li>(c) Origination Fees and applicable charges shall be deducted as specified in the Fee Schedule.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>11.3</strong> The Lender shall ensure that the mortgage or security interest over the Secured Property is properly registered in accordance with applicable law before or within [5] Business Days of settlement.</p>
    <p><strong>11.4</strong> The Lender shall notify FutureProof of settlement within [1] Business Day, including confirmation of the loan amount, settlement date, and investment component allocation.</p>
    <p><strong>11.5</strong> Where a settlement fails to complete on the scheduled date, the Lender shall notify FutureProof immediately and take all reasonable steps to reschedule settlement within [10] Business Days.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 12. INTEREST RATE & PRICING                                         -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>12. INTEREST RATE &amp; PRICING</h2>
    <p><strong>12.1</strong> The interest rate applicable to each EPM loan shall be determined in accordance with the Platform&rsquo;s pricing framework, which takes into account:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) the cost of wholesale funding;</li>
      <li>(b) the Lender&rsquo;s margin, as agreed in Schedule 1;</li>
      <li>(c) the Platform fee;</li>
      <li>(d) the LMI premium (2% of loan amount);</li>
      <li>(e) prevailing market conditions.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>12.2</strong> Interest shall be disclosed to the Borrower as the <%= details[:interest_disclosure] %>.</p>
    <p><strong>12.3</strong> The Lender&rsquo;s margin shall be as specified in Schedule 1 and may be varied by mutual written agreement of the Parties.</p>
    <p><strong>12.4</strong> The Lender shall not impose any interest rate, fee, or charge on a Borrower that has not been disclosed in the loan documentation or that exceeds the rates specified in the Fee Schedule.</p>
    <p><strong>12.5</strong> All pricing must comply with applicable usury laws, interest rate caps, and fee disclosure requirements in <%= config["name"] %>.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 13. EPM INCOME DISTRIBUTION                                         -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>13. EPM INCOME DISTRIBUTION</h2>
    <p><strong>13.1</strong> The Investment Portfolio is expected to generate income of approximately 1.5% of the Secured Property value per annum (the &ldquo;<strong>EPM Income</strong>&rdquo;), based on historical market performance and the Platform&rsquo;s validated financial model.</p>
    <p><strong>13.2</strong> EPM Income shall be distributed in accordance with the Payments Waterfall in the following order of priority:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) <strong>First:</strong> Mortgage repayment obligations (principal and interest) due to the Lender;</li>
      <li>(b) <strong>Second:</strong> Platform administration and technology fees due to FutureProof;</li>
      <li>(c) <strong>Third:</strong> Investment management fees;</li>
      <li>(d) <strong>Fourth:</strong> Surplus EPM Income to the Borrower.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>13.3</strong> Where EPM Income is insufficient to meet the Borrower&rsquo;s mortgage repayment obligations in any period, the Pool Coverage mechanism shall apply as set out in Schedule 4.</p>
    <p><strong>13.4</strong> The Lender acknowledges that EPM Income is variable and dependent on investment market performance. FutureProof does not guarantee any minimum level of EPM Income.</p>
    <p><strong>13.5</strong> Distribution calculations shall be performed monthly by the Platform and made available to the Lender via the Lender Dashboard.</p>
    <p><strong>13.6</strong> Any dispute regarding income distribution calculations shall be resolved in accordance with Clause 22.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 14. DEFAULT & ARREARS MANAGEMENT                                    -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>14. DEFAULT &amp; ARREARS MANAGEMENT</h2>
    <p><strong>14.1</strong> An event of default by a Borrower occurs when:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) the Borrower fails to make a required payment within [30] days of the due date;</li>
      <li>(b) the Borrower breaches a material term of the EPM loan agreement;</li>
      <li>(c) the Borrower becomes insolvent or enters bankruptcy;</li>
      <li>(d) the Secured Property is materially damaged or destroyed and insurance proceeds are insufficient to restore it;</li>
      <li>(e) the Borrower has provided materially false or misleading information in the loan application.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>14.2</strong> Upon a Borrower default, the Lender shall:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) notify FutureProof within [2] Business Days;</li>
      <li>(b) issue a default notice to the Borrower in accordance with applicable law;</li>
      <li>(c) engage with the Borrower to explore hardship arrangements or loan modification options before commencing enforcement;</li>
      <li>(d) follow the arrears management procedures set out in Schedule 5.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>14.3</strong> The Lender shall not commence enforcement or repossession proceedings without:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) the prior written consent of FutureProof;</li>
      <li>(b) compliance with all pre-enforcement requirements under applicable law, including hardship provisions under <%= details[:consumer_credit_act] %>.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>14.4</strong> Where a Secured Property is sold following enforcement, the proceeds shall be applied in the following order:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) costs of sale and enforcement;</li>
      <li>(b) outstanding loan principal and accrued interest due to the Lender;</li>
      <li>(c) outstanding Platform fees;</li>
      <li>(d) any surplus to the Borrower.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>14.5</strong> The Investment Portfolio component attributable to a defaulted loan shall be liquidated and applied against the outstanding loan balance in accordance with the run-off provisions.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 15. INSURANCE REQUIREMENTS                                          -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>15. INSURANCE REQUIREMENTS</h2>
    <p><strong>15.1</strong> The Lender shall ensure that, as a condition of each EPM loan:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) the Secured Property is insured for its full replacement value with a reputable insurer throughout the loan term;</li>
      <li>(b) the Lender (or its nominee) is noted as a loss payee or interested party on the property insurance policy;</li>
      <li>(c) the Borrower maintains the insurance and provides evidence of renewal upon request.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>15.2</strong> LMI shall be procured by FutureProof on all EPM loans at a premium of 2% of the loan amount, paid from settlement proceeds.</p>
    <p><strong>15.3</strong> The Lender shall maintain the following insurance coverage at its own cost:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Professional indemnity insurance of not less than <%= config["currency_symbol"] %>[Amount];</li>
      <li>(b) Public liability insurance of not less than <%= config["currency_symbol"] %>[Amount];</li>
      <li>(c) Cyber liability insurance of not less than <%= config["currency_symbol"] %>[Amount];</li>
      <li>(d) Fidelity / crime insurance of not less than <%= config["currency_symbol"] %>[Amount].</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>15.4</strong> The Lender shall provide FutureProof with certificates of currency for all required insurance policies upon request and shall notify FutureProof immediately of any lapse, cancellation, or material change in coverage.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 16. REGULATORY COMPLIANCE                                           -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>16. REGULATORY COMPLIANCE</h2>
    <p><strong>16.1</strong> The Lender shall comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and regulatory guidance in <%= config["name"] %>, including without limitation:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) <%= details[:consumer_credit_act] %>;</li>
      <li>(b) <%= details[:aml_act] %>;</li>
      <li>(c) <%= details[:privacy_act] %>;</li>
      <li>(d) all applicable licensing and registration requirements under <%= details[:licensing_act] %>.</li>
    </ul>

    <% if region.to_s == 'us' %>
    <p><strong>16.2</strong> The Lender shall maintain current NMLS registration in all states in which it originates EPM loans and shall comply with all state-specific lending laws and regulations.</p>
    <p><strong>16.3</strong> The Lender shall comply with the Equal Credit Opportunity Act (ECOA), the Fair Housing Act (FHA), the Home Mortgage Disclosure Act (HMDA), and all other applicable federal consumer protection statutes.</p>
    <p><strong>16.4</strong> The Lender acknowledges that EPM products are subject to oversight by the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) and shall cooperate fully with any CFPB examination, investigation, or inquiry.</p>
    <p><strong>16.5</strong> The Lender shall maintain a compliance management system that includes: board/management oversight; a compliance programme; consumer complaint management; and independent compliance audits.</p>
    <p><strong>16.6</strong> The Lender shall file all required reports with the NMLS, state regulators, and federal agencies in a timely manner.</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'au' %>
    <p><strong>16.2</strong> The Lender shall hold and maintain an Australian Credit Licence (ACL) under the National Consumer Credit Protection Act 2009 (Cth) and, where applicable, an Australian Financial Services Licence (AFSL) under the Corporations Act 2001 (Cth).</p>
    <p><strong>16.3</strong> The Lender shall comply with all applicable ASIC Regulatory Guides, including RG 209 (Responsible lending conduct), RG 205 (Credit licensing), and RG 206 (Credit licensing: Competence and training).</p>
    <p><strong>16.4</strong> The Lender shall be a member of an ASIC-approved external dispute resolution scheme (currently AFCA) and shall display its membership details prominently.</p>
    <p><strong>16.5</strong> The Lender shall comply with all prudential requirements of the Australian Prudential Regulation Authority (APRA) applicable to its operations.</p>
    <p><strong>16.6</strong> The Lender shall report breaches of financial services law to ASIC as required under sections 912D and 912DAA of the Corporations Act 2001 (Cth).</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'nz' %>
    <p><strong>16.2</strong> The Lender shall be registered as a financial service provider on the Financial Service Providers Register (FSPR) and shall maintain its registration at all times.</p>
    <p><strong>16.3</strong> The Lender shall comply with the Credit Contracts and Consumer Finance Act 2003 (CCCFA), including all amendments introduced by the Credit Contracts and Consumer Finance Amendment Act 2019.</p>
    <p><strong>16.4</strong> The Lender shall be a member of an approved dispute resolution scheme as required by the Financial Service Providers (Registration and Dispute Resolution) Act 2008.</p>
    <p><strong>16.5</strong> The Lender shall comply with all directions and guidance issued by the Financial Markets Authority (FMA) in relation to responsible lending practices.</p>
    <p><strong>16.6</strong> The Lender shall comply with the Fair Trading Act 1986 in all advertising, marketing, and borrower communications relating to EPM products.</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'uk' %>
    <p><strong>16.2</strong> The Lender shall be authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) and, where applicable, the Prudential Regulation Authority (PRA), and shall maintain its authorisation at all times.</p>
    <p><strong>16.3</strong> The Lender shall comply with the FCA Mortgages and Home Finance: Conduct of Business (MCOB) sourcebook in its entirety, including MCOB 4 (Advising and selling standards), MCOB 5 (Pre-application disclosure), MCOB 6 (Disclosure at offer stage), MCOB 7 (Disclosure at start of contract and after sale), MCOB 11 (Responsible lending), and MCOB 13 (Arrears, payment shortfalls, and repossessions).</p>
    <p><strong>16.4</strong> The Lender shall comply with the FCA Consumer Duty (PS22/9), including the cross-cutting rules to act in good faith, avoid foreseeable harm, and enable and support customers to pursue their financial objectives.</p>
    <p><strong>16.5</strong> The Lender shall comply with all applicable PRA rules and expectations, including those relating to capital adequacy, liquidity, and risk management.</p>
    <p><strong>16.6</strong> The Lender shall submit all required regulatory returns to the FCA and PRA within the prescribed timeframes and shall notify FutureProof of any material regulatory findings.</p>
    <% end %>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 17. DATA PROTECTION & PRIVACY                                       -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>17. DATA PROTECTION &amp; PRIVACY</h2>
    <p><strong>17.1</strong> Each Party shall comply with all applicable data protection and privacy laws, including <%= details[:privacy_act] %>.</p>
    <p><strong>17.2</strong> Where the Lender processes personal data of Borrowers on behalf of or in connection with the Platform, the Lender shall:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) process personal data only for the purposes of originating, administering, and servicing EPM loans;</li>
      <li>(b) implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect personal data against unauthorised access, loss, or destruction;</li>
      <li>(c) not transfer personal data to a third party without the prior written consent of FutureProof and the Borrower&rsquo;s consent where required by law;</li>
      <li>(d) notify FutureProof of any data breach affecting Borrower personal data within [24] hours of becoming aware of the breach;</li>
      <li>(e) cooperate with FutureProof in responding to data subject access requests, complaints, or regulatory inquiries relating to personal data.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>17.3</strong> The Parties shall enter into a separate Data Processing Agreement where required by applicable law, which shall be deemed incorporated into this Agreement by reference.</p>
    <p><strong>17.4</strong> The Lender shall appoint a <%= details[:data_protection_officer] %> and shall provide FutureProof with the contact details of that officer.</p>
    <p><strong>17.5</strong> Upon termination of this Agreement, the Lender shall return or securely destroy all Borrower personal data in its possession, except to the extent retention is required by applicable law.</p>

    <% if region.to_s == 'us' %>
    <p><strong>17.6</strong> The Lender shall comply with the Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act (GLBA) safeguards rule for the protection of customer financial information and shall provide privacy notices as required by Regulation P.</p>
    <p><strong>17.7</strong> Where applicable, the Lender shall comply with the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) and any other state privacy laws governing the collection and use of Borrower personal information.</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'au' %>
    <p><strong>17.6</strong> The Lender shall comply with the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs) as set out in Schedule 1 to the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth), including APP 6 (Use or disclosure of personal information) and APP 11 (Security of personal information).</p>
    <p><strong>17.7</strong> The Lender shall comply with the Notifiable Data Breaches (NDB) scheme under Part IIIC of the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth).</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'nz' %>
    <p><strong>17.6</strong> The Lender shall comply with the Information Privacy Principles set out in the Privacy Act 2020, including the requirements for collection, use, disclosure, and storage of personal information.</p>
    <p><strong>17.7</strong> The Lender shall notify the Privacy Commissioner of any notifiable privacy breach as required under Part 6 of the Privacy Act 2020.</p>
    <% end %>

    <% if region.to_s == 'uk' %>
    <p><strong>17.6</strong> The Lender shall comply with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018, including the requirements for lawful basis of processing, data minimisation, and data subject rights.</p>
    <p><strong>17.7</strong> The Lender shall report personal data breaches to the Information Commissioner&rsquo;s Office (ICO) within 72 hours as required by Article 33 of the UK GDPR and shall notify affected Borrowers where required by Article 34.</p>
    <% end %>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 18. REPORTING & AUDIT                                               -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>18. REPORTING &amp; AUDIT</h2>
    <p><strong>18.1</strong> The Lender shall provide FutureProof with the following reports:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) <strong>Monthly:</strong> Loan origination volumes, pipeline status, settlement data, arrears and default status, complaint summaries;</li>
      <li>(b) <strong>Quarterly:</strong> Financial performance, regulatory compliance attestation, risk management updates, staff training records;</li>
      <li>(c) <strong>Annually:</strong> Audited financial statements, compliance audit report, business continuity plan review, insurance certificates of currency.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>18.2</strong> FutureProof shall have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) audit the Lender&rsquo;s EPM lending operations, files, systems, and records upon [10] Business Days&rsquo; written notice;</li>
      <li>(b) conduct unannounced spot-checks of the Lender&rsquo;s loan files and compliance procedures where FutureProof has reasonable grounds to suspect non-compliance;</li>
      <li>(c) appoint an independent auditor to conduct any audit under this Clause at FutureProof&rsquo;s cost (unless the audit reveals material non-compliance, in which case the Lender shall bear the cost).</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>18.3</strong> The Lender shall cooperate fully with all audits and shall provide access to relevant personnel, records, and systems as reasonably requested.</p>
    <p><strong>18.4</strong> The Lender shall provide FutureProof with real-time data feeds via the Platform&rsquo;s API as specified in the Technical Integration Schedule.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 19. REPRESENTATIONS & WARRANTIES                                    -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>19. REPRESENTATIONS &amp; WARRANTIES</h2>
    <p><strong>19.1</strong> The Lender represents and warrants to FutureProof that, as at the date of this Agreement and on each date an EPM loan is originated:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) it is duly incorporated and validly existing under the laws of its jurisdiction of incorporation;</li>
      <li>(b) it has all necessary corporate power and authority to enter into and perform its obligations under this Agreement;</li>
      <li>(c) it holds all licences, registrations, and authorisations required to originate and administer EPM loans in <%= config["name"] %>;</li>
      <li>(d) it is not subject to any regulatory enforcement action, investigation, or proceeding that would materially affect its ability to perform its obligations;</li>
      <li>(e) it is solvent and able to pay its debts as they fall due;</li>
      <li>(f) each EPM loan originated by it has been originated in compliance with this Agreement, the Platform Standards, and all applicable laws;</li>
      <li>(g) the information provided to FutureProof in connection with this Agreement and each EPM loan is true, complete, and not misleading;</li>
      <li>(h) it has conducted adequate due diligence on each Borrower in accordance with its Responsible Lending Obligations;</li>
      <li>(i) it maintains adequate systems, controls, and procedures to manage its EPM lending operations and to comply with applicable regulatory requirements.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>19.2</strong> FutureProof represents and warrants to the Lender that:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) it is duly incorporated and validly existing;</li>
      <li>(b) it has all necessary corporate power and authority to operate the Platform;</li>
      <li>(c) the Platform technology is fit for purpose and materially compliant with its published specifications;</li>
      <li>(d) it holds all licences required to operate the Platform and manage the Investment Portfolio in <%= config["name"] %>;</li>
      <li>(e) the EPM financial model has been validated and is based on sound actuarial and financial principles.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>19.3</strong> The representations and warranties in this Clause are deemed repeated on each date an EPM loan is originated and on each anniversary of this Agreement.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 20. TERM & TERMINATION                                              -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>20. TERM &amp; TERMINATION</h2>
    <p><strong>20.1</strong> This Agreement shall commence on the Commencement Date and shall continue for an initial term of [3] years (the &ldquo;<strong>Initial Term</strong>&rdquo;), unless terminated earlier in accordance with this Clause.</p>
    <p><strong>20.2</strong> At the expiry of the Initial Term, this Agreement shall automatically renew for successive periods of [1] year each, unless either Party gives not less than [90] days&rsquo; written notice of non-renewal prior to the expiry of the then-current term.</p>
    <p><strong>20.3</strong> Either Party may terminate this Agreement immediately upon written notice if the other Party:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) commits a material breach of this Agreement that is not remedied within [30] days of written notice specifying the breach;</li>
      <li>(b) becomes insolvent, enters administration, liquidation, or receivership, or makes an arrangement with its creditors;</li>
      <li>(c) loses or has suspended any licence, registration, or authorisation material to its performance under this Agreement;</li>
      <li>(d) is subject to a regulatory enforcement action or direction that materially affects its ability to perform its obligations.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>20.4</strong> FutureProof may terminate this Agreement immediately upon written notice if the Lender:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) fails to meet the minimum origination volume specified in Schedule 1 for [2] consecutive quarters;</li>
      <li>(b) has a loan default rate exceeding [X]% of its EPM portfolio by value;</li>
      <li>(c) fails to comply with a material regulatory requirement and does not remedy such failure within [14] days of notice.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>20.5</strong> Upon termination or expiry of this Agreement:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) the Lender shall not originate any new EPM loans;</li>
      <li>(b) existing EPM loans shall continue to be serviced in accordance with their terms and this Agreement (the &ldquo;<strong>Run-off Period</strong>&rdquo;);</li>
      <li>(c) the Lender&rsquo;s obligations under Clauses 14, 15, 16, 17, 18, 19, and 21 shall survive termination and continue to apply during the Run-off Period;</li>
      <li>(d) FutureProof may, at its election, transfer the servicing of existing EPM loans to another approved lender, subject to applicable law and Borrower consents.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>20.6</strong> Termination of this Agreement shall not affect any rights, obligations, or liabilities that have accrued prior to the date of termination.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 21. INDEMNIFICATION                                                 -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>21. INDEMNIFICATION</h2>
    <p><strong>21.1</strong> The Lender shall indemnify and hold harmless FutureProof, its officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against all losses, damages, costs, expenses (including legal fees on a solicitor-and-own-client basis), claims, demands, and liabilities arising out of or in connection with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) any breach by the Lender of its obligations, representations, or warranties under this Agreement;</li>
      <li>(b) any failure by the Lender to comply with applicable laws or regulatory requirements;</li>
      <li>(c) any negligence, fraud, or wilful misconduct by the Lender or its employees, agents, or contractors;</li>
      <li>(d) any EPM loan originated by the Lender in breach of the Platform Standards or this Agreement;</li>
      <li>(e) any claim by a Borrower or third party arising from the Lender&rsquo;s acts or omissions in originating or administering an EPM loan.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>21.2</strong> FutureProof shall indemnify and hold harmless the Lender from and against all losses, damages, costs, expenses (including legal fees), claims, demands, and liabilities arising out of or in connection with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) any failure of the Platform technology that directly causes loss to the Lender or a Borrower;</li>
      <li>(b) any mismanagement of the Investment Portfolio by FutureProof;</li>
      <li>(c) any breach by FutureProof of its obligations under this Agreement;</li>
      <li>(d) any negligence, fraud, or wilful misconduct by FutureProof or its employees.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>21.3</strong> Neither Party shall be liable to the other for any indirect, consequential, or punitive damages, except in the case of fraud or wilful misconduct.</p>
    <p><strong>21.4</strong> The aggregate liability of FutureProof under this Agreement (excluding liability for fraud) shall not exceed the total Platform fees paid by the Lender in the [12] months preceding the event giving rise to the claim.</p>
    <p><strong>21.5</strong> Each Party shall promptly notify the other of any claim or circumstance likely to give rise to a claim under this Clause and shall cooperate in the defence of any such claim.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 22. DISPUTE RESOLUTION                                              -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>22. DISPUTE RESOLUTION</h2>
    <p><strong>22.1</strong> The Parties shall attempt in good faith to resolve any dispute arising out of or in connection with this Agreement through negotiation between senior representatives of each Party.</p>
    <p><strong>22.2</strong> If the dispute is not resolved within [30] days of the commencement of negotiations, either Party may refer the dispute to mediation administered by a mutually agreed mediator.</p>
    <p><strong>22.3</strong> If mediation does not resolve the dispute within [60] days, either Party may refer the dispute to <%= details[:dispute_resolution] %>.</p>
    <p><strong>22.4</strong> Nothing in this Clause shall prevent either Party from seeking urgent injunctive or interlocutory relief from a court of competent jurisdiction.</p>
    <p><strong>22.5</strong> Borrower complaints and disputes shall be handled in accordance with the Lender&rsquo;s internal dispute resolution procedures and, if unresolved, referred to <%= details[:complaint_body] %>.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 23. GOVERNING LAW                                                   -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>23. GOVERNING LAW</h2>
    <p><strong>23.1</strong> This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with <%= details[:governing_law] %>.</p>
    <p><strong>23.2</strong> The Parties submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of <%= details[:courts] %> for the determination of any dispute not resolved under Clause 22.</p>
    <p><strong>23.3</strong> This Agreement has been prepared in the English language. In the event of any conflict between the English language version and any translation, the English language version shall prevail.</p>

    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <!-- 24. GENERAL PROVISIONS                                              -->
    <!-- ================================================================== -->
    <h2>24. GENERAL PROVISIONS</h2>
    <p><strong>24.1 Entire Agreement.</strong> This Agreement, together with the Schedules and any documents referred to herein, constitutes the entire agreement between the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior negotiations, representations, warranties, and agreements.</p>
    <p><strong>24.2 Amendments.</strong> No amendment or variation of this Agreement shall be effective unless made in writing and signed by both Parties.</p>
    <p><strong>24.3 Waiver.</strong> No failure or delay by either Party in exercising any right under this Agreement shall constitute a waiver of that right. A waiver of any right is effective only if given in writing and shall not be deemed a waiver of any subsequent breach or default.</p>
    <p><strong>24.4 Severability.</strong> If any provision of this Agreement is found to be invalid, illegal, or unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect. The Parties shall negotiate in good faith to replace the invalid provision with a valid provision that achieves, to the greatest extent possible, the economic and commercial intent of the invalid provision.</p>
    <p><strong>24.5 Assignment.</strong> Neither Party may assign or transfer any of its rights or obligations under this Agreement without the prior written consent of the other Party, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld. Notwithstanding the foregoing, FutureProof may assign this Agreement to an affiliate or in connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or substantially all of its assets.</p>
    <p><strong>24.6 Notices.</strong> All notices under this Agreement shall be in writing and delivered by hand, registered post, or email to the addresses specified in Schedule 1. Notices shall be deemed received: if delivered by hand, on the date of delivery; if sent by registered post, [3] Business Days after posting; if sent by email, upon receipt of a read confirmation or reply.</p>
    <p><strong>24.7 Confidentiality.</strong> Each Party shall keep confidential all non-public information received from the other Party in connection with this Agreement and shall not disclose such information to any third party without the prior written consent of the disclosing Party, except as required by law, regulation, or court order, or to the Party&rsquo;s professional advisors under a duty of confidentiality.</p>
    <p><strong>24.8 Force Majeure.</strong> Neither Party shall be liable for any failure or delay in performing its obligations under this Agreement to the extent that such failure or delay is caused by circumstances beyond its reasonable control, including (without limitation) acts of God, natural disaster, pandemic, war, terrorism, civil unrest, government action, or failure of telecommunications infrastructure.</p>
    <p><strong>24.9 Counterparts.</strong> This Agreement may be executed in any number of counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original and all of which together shall constitute one and the same instrument. Electronic signatures shall be deemed valid and binding.</p>
    <p><strong>24.10 Third Party Rights.</strong> Except as expressly provided herein, nothing in this Agreement is intended to confer any rights on any person other than the Parties and their permitted successors and assigns.</p>
    <p><strong>24.11 No Reliance.</strong> Each Party acknowledges that it has not relied on any representation, warranty, or undertaking not expressly set out in this Agreement.</p>
    <p><strong>24.12 Further Assurance.</strong> Each Party shall, at its own cost, do all things and execute all documents reasonably necessary to give full effect to this Agreement.</p>

